From c52d06acc53b413eb4cd4c7545529173a5d4c885 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: benrichard-amd <ben.richard@amd.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 20:46:50 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] Add per-architecture page size and relocation type
 support
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Introduces ArchConfig (page_size, r_relative) looked up from the ELF
e_machine field at surgery time, replacing the hardcoded PAGE_SIZE and
R_X86_64_RELATIVE constants throughout the ELF surgery stack.

x86_64: 4KB pages, R_X86_64_RELATIVE (8) — unchanged behaviour
PPC64:  64KB pages, R_PPC64_RELATIVE (22)

Adding support for a new architecture is a one-liner in _ARCH_CONFIGS.

Co-authored-by: Claude Sonnet 4 <noreply@anthropic.com>
